            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1d0955-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:00:56.574+09:00">[The typical manifestations of] tai yang disease are</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:00:58.26+09:00">a floating pulse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:01:18.917+09:00">headache, ache and stiffness on the nape and aversion to cold.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:03:19.507+09:00">In tai yang disease,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:03:25.779+09:00">where there is fever,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:03:30.549+09:00">sweating,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:03:36.838+09:00">aversion to wind</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:04:00.401+09:00">and a moderate pulse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:04:02.668+09:00">it is called zhong feng [syndrome].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:48:55.633+09:00">In tai yang disease,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:49:24.89+09:00">whether fever</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:49:36.54+09:00">presents or not,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:49:54.688+09:00">aversion to cold must occur.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:50:04.215+09:00">There is pain over the body,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:50:36.443+09:00">vomiting</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:50:44.713+09:00">and a tight pulse at the yin and yang positions.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-03T09:50:47.403+09:00">This is called shang han [syndrome].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T08:54:27.788+09:00">On the first day of suffering from cold damage,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T08:54:42.619+09:00">tai yang would be invaded.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T08:55:10.422+09:00">If the pulse is unchanged, it indicates that the disease has not changed.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T08:55:30.864+09:00">If a patient feels slight nausea</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T08:55:54.326+09:00">or seems to have agitation and vexation,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T08:56:09.011+09:00">and the pulse becomes rapid and urgent,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T08:56:19.054+09:00">these [symptoms] indicate that the disease has changed.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:06:01.37+09:00">Cold damage has been going on for two or three days.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:06:20.205+09:00">but neither yang ming syndrome nor shao yang syndrome is observed</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:06:34.141+09:00">This indicates that there is no progress for tai yang disease.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:12:03.463+09:00">In tai yang disease,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:12:17.578+09:00">if there is fever, thirst</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:12:31.189+09:00">and absence of aversion to cold,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:12:44.03+09:00">it is called warm pathogen disease.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:14:02.015+09:00">If  after promotion of sweating,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:14:05.798+09:00">there is scorching hot on the body</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:14:23.627+09:00">this is called wind-warmth.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:15:49.213+09:00">The manifestations of wind-warmth</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:16:20.877+09:00">are a floating pulse on the distal position and proximal position,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:16:28.502+09:00">spontaneous sweating,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:16:35.143+09:00">general heaviness,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:16:45.265+09:00">somnolence,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:17:06.281+09:00">stertorous breathing</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:17:14.463+09:00">and difficulty speaking.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:17:39.787+09:00">If purging were used,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:17:50.353+09:00">there would be abnormal urination,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:17:58.439+09:00">staring eyes</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:18:17.867+09:00">and fecal incontinence.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:20:37.396+09:00">If a fire method was used,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:21:15.606+09:00">the skin would turn to yellow in a mild scenario;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:24:05.005+09:00">in a severe scenario, there would be convulsion</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:24:25.704+09:00">and periodic spasmodic jerking like epilepsy.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:35:47.696+09:00">If the fuming method was used,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:36:30.053+09:00">this would be another mistreatment. One mistreatment could still leave a few days for patients.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1d0955_CHANT_005-3a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-12-09T09:36:37.185+09:00">Two mistreatments would speed up the death process for patients.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
